Homicide detectives at the Federal Capital Territory (FCT) Police Command have arrested Terungwa Edward Achado, the husband of the late member of the National Youth Service Corps (NYSC), Stephanie Se-ember Terungwa Edward Achado in respect of her death. The late Stephanie, who left behind a baby, was declared missing on April 14 in Abuja but was later found dead with her body dismembered. 

File Photo



Her body was found kitted in NYSC uniform, about two weeks after she disappeared in the Lokogoma area of the territory. The incident triggered reactions from concerned Nigerians and fear amongst corps members serving in the nation’s capital. According to DAILY POST, following the ongoing investigation to uncover the root cause of the corps member’s death, the husband, Terungwa Edward Achado and others are currently in police custody. The husband and two others who last called the phone number of the victim were said to have been arrested on Saturday.